title: Watch: Mount Etna erupts in fiery show of lava
text:
Tuesday, February 28, 2017, 16:12 by PA Watch: Mount Etna erupts in fiery show of lava Volcano roars after being dormant for two years You need Javascript and either Adobe Flash or Html5 to view this video. Video: Reuters Photo: PA Photo: PA 
Bright lava lit up the night sky on the Italian island of Sicily today as Mount Etna erupted for the first time this year. 
The volcano, one of the most active in the world, has been largely dormant for the last two years, but it sprung to life with bright orange lava spewing out high over the Mediterranean Island, eventually easing off by this morning. 
Catania airport, situated within 50 km (31 miles) of the volcano, remained open, but authorities were tracking the movements of the ash cloud. 
Etna, at 3,330 metres (10,926 feet), is the highest volcano in mainland Europe and can burst into action several times a year. The last major eruption was in 1992. Photo: PA Â« Watch: Dramatic video shows deadly California plane crash Advert
